1
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:36,760
Sister Xin, food's here.

2
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,600
I spoke with the chairman.

3
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,720
We talked.

4
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,680
And he agreed.

5
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,200
Well, isn't that great?

6
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,480
Why aren't you happy?

7
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,320
I gave up my company dividends

8
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,520
to get him to agree.

9
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,200
Until the Blind Boxes turn a profit,

10
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,520
I won't take any dividends.

11
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,840
Why should you?

12
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,640
Sister Xin, you're making money for the company.

13
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,440
Why sacrifice your own interests?

14
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,880
Dayazhai's thread-bound books and fine art prints

15
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:11,360
have hit a bottleneck.

16
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,160
If I don't seize this chance,

17
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,080
we won't grow much further.

18
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,520
You only think about the company.

19
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,120
Does anyone think about you?

20
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,280
Don't worry.

21
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,840
I trust my own judgment.

22
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:25,920
Once the Blind Boxes take off,

23
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,640
they won't shortchange me a cent.

24
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,520
The Dayazhai Xuan Paper Blind Box launch

25
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,680
now begins.

26
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,240
Let's invite our four leaders to unveil it.

27
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:48,360
Next,

28
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,440
let's welcome our talented designer

29
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,720
to explain the design concept.

30
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,560
I'm Xuan Yan, the designer of these products.

31
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,880
When I designed them,

32
00:02:56,880 --> 00:03:00,680
I drew from Tang Dynasty Court Lady Paintings

33
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,280
and the Twelve Beauties from Dream of the Red Chamber.

34
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,280
They represent

35
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,440
young people expressing their attitude,

36
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,040
a sense of rebellion.

37
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:19,920
Old Xuan,

38
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,560
I offered a toast to the heavens,

39
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,280
and the heavens said,

40
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,280
one rain, then a week of sun.

41
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,200
Then another rain,

42
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,080
and another week of sunshine.

43
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,280
Take a look.

44
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,160
Isn't this great?

45
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,280
So white!

46
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:37,920
In all these years,

47
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,360
we've never made processed bark this white.

48
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,080
Right.

49
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:44,680
That's why you need real expertise.

50
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,080
For good paper,

51
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:49,680
the raw materials must be top-notch.

52
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,520
You're absolutely right.

53
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,240
Master Lin.

54
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,800
Sister-in-law, sister-in-law.

55
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,040
You didn't have to bring gifts.

56
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:56,920
Why bother?

57
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:59,480
How could I come empty-handed?

58
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,640
You barely come down the mountain all year.

59
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,920
Old Xuan and I kept saying we'd visit,

60
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,360
but we've been so busy

61
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,080
we never made it up here.

62
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,640
I wasn't sure what you needed.

63
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,920
What could I possibly need?

64
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,920
I've got sky, earth, and sandalwood trees.

65
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,320
I lack nothing.

66
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,519
You can't make me take it back.

67
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:18,880
Just take it.

68
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,920
It's chilly on the mountain.

69
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,800
Something to keep out the cold.

70
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:22,600
Right.

71
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,800
Aren't your knees bad?

72
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:30,880
I brought you pure wool knee warmers.

73
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:31,880
Wear them.

74
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,320
They're warm.

75
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:37,080
Manager Xu, don't force it.

76
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,760
If you truly don't want Xuan Family paper,

77
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,640
then let's just drop the deal.

78
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,080
Please don't, Boss Xuan.

79
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:51,360
The Palace Museum wants Ancient-Method Paper.

80
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:54,120
Can't you just make some?

81
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:55,920
Think about it.

82
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,680
Whether it's handmade paper or Ancient-Method Paper,

83
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,600
none of the profit goes to outsiders.

84
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,640
It all stays in the Xuan Family's fields.

85
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,960
Our boss heard your paper is excellent

86
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,960
and solved the Palace Museum's problem.

87
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,200
He decided right there

88
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:12,480
that Pine Crane Studio's handmade paper

89
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,080
will all come from the Xuan Family.

90
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:17,640
Now you're saying the deal is off?

91
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,840
How am I supposed to explain this?

92
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,320
Manager Xu,

93
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,360
I'm not trying to make things hard for you.

94
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,920
I told you last time,

95
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,800
the Xuan Family doesn't make Ancient-Method Paper.

96
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:03,680
Master.

97
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,800
Just say what you need to.

98
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,000
Manager Xu...

99
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,480
called you, right?

100
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,680
Manager Xu called me too.

101
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,040
Manager Xu said

102
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:29,000
The Palace Museum decided to use Ancient-Method Paper.

103
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,640
Their chairman is very pleased.

104
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:34,760
He made the call:

105
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,240
all handmade Xuan paper will be ordered from the Xuan family.

106
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,120
That's four or five million in orders a year.

107
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,040
Manager Xu also said

108
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,520
Pine Crane Studio's domestic and international resources

109
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,000
will all be available to us.

110
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,720
They'll also help us take part

111
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:48,440
in various awards at home and abroad,

112
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,480
and exchange events too.

113
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:52,200
State-level occasions and the UN

114
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,720
can all use Xuan family paper from now on.

115
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,160
As long as this partnership works out,

116
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,360
the Xuan family's position in the Xuan paper world

117
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,680
will be rock solid.

118
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:02,640
I've already told

119
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,600
Pine Crane Studio

120
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,480
we're not doing the deal.

121
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,200
Manager Xu also said,

122
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,120
if we don't cooperate,

123
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,680
he can't answer to the chairman.

124
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,760
And any other cooperation will be off the table.

125
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,440
What's that supposed to mean?

126
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,760
Are they threatening us now?

127
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,240
Who do they think they are?

128
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,160
Pathetic.

129
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,240
I know you're biased against Ancient-Method Paper.

130
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,240
That's what I really don't get.

131
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,040
We say it every single day,

132
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,520
"honor the ancestors, honor the ancestors."

133
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,560
Ancient-Method Paper is the paper our ancestors made!

134
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:47,880
Reviving Ancient-Method Paper,

135
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,160
isn't that honoring the ancestors?

136
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,680
And what's more,

137
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:53,240
consumers recognize the Xuan family brand,

138
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,320
and what they recognize is

139
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,320
the Xuan family's thousand-year-old craft.

140
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,880
If we abandon what our ancestors gave us

141
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,360
to make paper that's neither truly handmade

142
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,560
nor properly machine-made,

143
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,560
how can we live up to...

144
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,240
Enough! Enough! Enough!

145
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,840
Master, we can't keep...

146
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,640
You, shut your mouth!

147
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,680
It's not your place to speak in the Xuan family.

148
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,520
A traitor like you who betrays his master and ancestors

149
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:18,080
should've been dragged out and beaten to death long ago.

150
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:19,120
Sit down.

151
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:19,920
Don't hold me back.

152
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:20,720
Alright, alright.

153
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:24,360
Eat your food.

154
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,800
Brother Xuan,

155
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,360
I don't get it either.

156
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:30,520
Someone this treacherous,

157
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,320
just kick him out already.

158
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:34,600
Don't touch me.

159
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,640
Don't touch me.

160
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:36,760
I'm telling you for the last time,

161
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:37,559
don't touch me.

162
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,559
So what if I touch you?

163
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:39,760
You want another beating?

164
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,240
Try me again!

165
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,000
Sit properly.

166
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,760
Sit, sit, sit.

167
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:42,559
Eat.

168
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,320
Sit back down.

169
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:50,000
Yongnian, things have gotten this bad,

170
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,680
you can't keep indulging him.

171
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,520
Everyone, sit down.

172
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,120
Zhang Du, go on.

173
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,560
You people are really something.

174
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,120
All you can do is sit there acting self-righteous and blame me.

175
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:11,360
Tell me,

176
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:13,760
who among you has truly thought about the Xuan family?

177
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,760
What are you saying?

178
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,680
We're talking about saving the Xuan family.

179
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:17,680
Come up with a plan yourself.

180
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,080
If you can, then I'll...

181
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:22,960
And you,

182
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,640
how about I dock your pay one month?

183
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:27,640
What's wrong with getting paid for drying paper?

184
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,560
If the Xuan family is gone,

185
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,680
what wages will there be to collect?

186
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,920
When the Xuan family was in trouble,

187
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,000
I didn't take a single cent.

188
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:42,520
I'm the only one truly thinking of the Xuan family.

189
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,680
Why do I insist so much on Ancient-Method Paper?

190
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,840
Because Ancient-Method Paper

191
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,040
is the foundation of the Xuan family's survival.

192
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,240
I dare speak to Master like this

193
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,720
because I have a clear conscience.

194
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,080
I'm the only one thinking about

195
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,360
how to make the Xuan family flourish.

196
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,280
You might as well just say it,

197
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,160
only you are qualified to be the Xuan heir.

198
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,360
You got that right.

199
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,840
That's exactly what I think.

200
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:09,120
Only I am qualified to be the Xuan heir.

201
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,200
Look at that, look at that.

202
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,240
Talking all high and mighty,

203
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,840
and now your true colors are showing.

204
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:14,800
Enough, enough.

205
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,760
Are you done?

206
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:20,680
I'm done.

207
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,720
Our Xuan family,

208
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,960
the paper we've made through the ages,

209
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,040
has always been by ancient method.

210
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,040
It's just that

211
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,120
we make ancient method with tradition and innovation,

212
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:40,880
not the rigid, stuck-in-the-past ancient method.

213
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,160
Zhang Du.

214
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,360
Let me show you around.

215
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:55,880
Let's start with the raw materials.

216
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,480
These here,

217
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:02,120
they have to be exposed to sun and rain,

218
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,720
then soaked in lime to bleach,

219
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:08,960
and then dried in the field for three years.

220
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,360
This is different from using bleach

221
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:13,400
and other chemical processes.

222
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,920
It's a whole different thing.

223
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:19,240
That's why we Xuans kept the drying field.

224
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,360
From selecting materials to processed bark and straw,

225
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:26,240
we've preserved the ancient methods.

226
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,880
This is pulp-making.

227
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,120
In the past, our ancestors

228
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:36,760
pounded the bark and straw by hand.

229
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,280
Later,

230
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,760
they invented water-wheel pounders.

231
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,720
Now we use electric pounders.

232
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:48,880
It saves several times the labor,

233
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,280
but the quality,

234
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,600
there's no difference at all.

235
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:54,840
Are you saying

236
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,760
that electric pounding isn't the ancient method,

237
00:11:57,760 --> 00:12:00,480
and only manual labor counts as ancient?

238
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,160
This pulp-washing pool

239
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,360
is connected with circulating water.

240
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:08,960
It's cleaner than the traditional bag method.

241
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,880
This Xuan paper,

242
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,520
its craftsmanship strives to be

243
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:17,160
light as cicada wings, white as snow.

244
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,880
This is our

245
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:24,000
pursuit of higher craftsmanship quality.

246
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,400
In the old days,

247
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,400
we'd take the paper

248
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:30,120
and dry it on bluestone slabs in the sun.

249
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,160
In a day,

250
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,480
we could only dry a dozen or so sheets,

251
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:35,000
a few dozen at most.

252
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:37,120
If it rained, we couldn't dry them at all.

253
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:38,880
Around here,

254
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,120
during the plum rain season,

255
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,720
it rains for a whole month straight.

256
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,280
Luckily, later on,

257
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:46,960
wood-fired and coal-fired drying walls appeared.

258
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:51,240
Now we've achieved electric drying walls.

259
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,840
It solves the clean energy issue,

260
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:57,680
and gives us precise temperature control.

261
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:02,600
The paper quality is far better than before.

262
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,880
So why wouldn't we use it?

263
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:10,680
You just don't understand my thinking.

264
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:14,400
What I care about is how to prove

265
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,600
the Xuan family's thousand-year heritage.

266
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,320
Ordinary folks don't understand it,

267
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,360
but they're willing to believe

268
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,600
that ancient methods equal heritage.

269
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,120
You're not making paper.

270
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,360
You're putting on a show, faking it.

271
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:31,360
That's a misunderstanding of me.

272
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,160
What I want to do

273
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:35,600
is bring glory back to the Xuan family.

274
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,000
Those things you make,

275
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:44,480
those Ancient-Method Paper videos,

276
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,120
if you say

277
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:49,760
all the paper sold is truly ancient method,

278
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:53,840
the price would be over ten thousand yuan.

279
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,520
Aside from The Palace Museum's special uses,

280
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,600
where else could it be used?

281
