710
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,360
Xuan paper has a thousand-year history.

711
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:11,280
From materials, formula, to production,

712
00:31:11,280 --> 00:31:12,840
has it all stayed exactly the same?

713
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,080
You've researched this your whole lives.

714
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:18,520
Don't let a gimmicky name like "Ancient-Method Paper"

715
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,360
pull the wool over your eyes.

716
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,040
This old fellow,

717
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:27,160
his mouth's been like a little knife all his life.

718
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,240
If he doesn't stab someone with it,

719
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:30,600
he feels uncomfortable inside.

720
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:33,840
This large-scale national treasure restoration

721
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:37,560
concerns these relics for generations to come.

722
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,520
Choosing the very best paper

723
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:42,000
is our duty and our attitude.

724
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:46,640
Come on, Old Jiang,

725
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,160
why are you getting angry?

726
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,320
This,

727
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:52,800
this is a serious matter.

728
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:56,000
Now that it's all been said,

729
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,560
and Old Jiang here has made his stance clear,

730
00:31:58,560 --> 00:31:59,160
right?

731
00:31:59,160 --> 00:32:00,560
We know where we stand.

732
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,000
We guarantee fairness and impartiality.

733
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:05,080
If you're not fair, I'll curse you to death.

734
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:06,880
Come on then.

735
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:07,640
Let's test the paper.

736
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,760
Come on, alright, test the paper.

737
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:09,840
Come on, come on, test the paper.

738
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:20,760
There's one thing I've never figured out.

739
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:21,680
Zhang Du.

740
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,760
Zhang Du, Zhang Du, Zhang Du.

741
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:30,600
Of all the things you could do,

742
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:33,320
why do you insist on becoming a master?

743
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,560
There's a good saying:

744
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:38,560
women fear marrying wrong, men fear the wrong trade.

745
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:40,880
If you really want to be a master,

746
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,920
be a master of the I Ching,

747
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:42,840
a master of Chinese classics,

748
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:44,320
you could even become a monastic master.

749
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:45,040
Right?

750
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,520
Isn't any of that a hundred times better than scooping paper?

751
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:48,400
Fine.

752
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:51,600
Even if you truly became a master at scooping paper,

753
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,960
you'd still just be a paper-scooper, wouldn't you?

754
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:05,560
Impressive.

755
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:12,720
This old fellow.

756
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,720
Really looks the part.

757
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:14,800
Absolutely flawless.

758
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:16,000
You can't help but admire it.

759
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:18,840
Never mind admiration for now.

760
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:21,400
You old-timers,

761
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:25,160
take a good look at these two sheets.

762
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:40,960
At a glance, they look identical.

763
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:42,880
But look closely,

764
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:44,760
