774
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:09,280
Come on, show off already.

775
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:10,800
Don't keep us waiting.

776
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,520
If you really want to know,

777
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,239
call those two young papermakers up here.

778
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,760
Ask them carefully what they were thinking.

779
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:24,600
Hello, respected judges.

780
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:25,960
Sit.

781
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:30,760
Xuan Yan.

782
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:32,000
Zhang Du.

783
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:36,360
Our expert panel

784
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,120
has analyzed the paper you two made,

785
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:40,440
covering both the physical-chemical aspects

786
00:34:40,440 --> 00:34:42,960
and the artistic aspects.

787
00:34:43,719 --> 00:34:45,960
We invited you here today

788
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,880
to have a proper chat with you.

789
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,440
In papermaking,

790
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:52,480
what insights and feelings have you gained?

791
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,679
Who'd like to go first?

792
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:56,960
Alright, I'll go first.

793
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:01,000
While making this ream of paper,

794
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,160
a poem suddenly

795
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:05,680
came to my mind.

796
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,240
I feel this poem

797
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:10,920
captures exactly how I felt at that moment.

798
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:12,400
A poem?

799
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:15,840
Alright then.

800
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:17,520
Share it with us.

801
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:18,560
Okay.

802
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:25,640
A curtain of snowy waves from deep mountains flows,

803
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:29,880
Through a thousand pounding strokes, greatness shows.

804
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,960
It seeks no glamour to compete with the world,

805
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:39,280
Leaving only pure spirit through heaven unfurled.

806
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:42,560
Quite good.

807
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:44,680
Using an object to express intent,

808
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:46,320
evoking emotion through imagery.

809
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:50,880
This poem of yours

810
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,520
imitates Wang Mian's "Ink Plum."

811
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,840
"Not seeking praise for its beautiful color,

812
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,200
Only leaving pure spirit filling heaven and earth."

813
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:01,120
Yours is "seeks no glamour to compete with the world,

814
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,440
Leaving only pure spirit through heaven unfurled."

815
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:06,000
You just swapped "Qiankun" for "Kunqian."

816
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:07,440
That works too, I suppose.

817
00:36:08,120 --> 00:36:09,720
Poems can be imitated too?

818
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:11,160
Of course they can.

819
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,120
However,

820
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:14,440
there's an ethical boundary here.

821
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:15,880
Originality increment,

822
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:17,720
degree of contextual reconstruction,

823
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,120
textual variation rate.

824
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:20,480
In "Yinchuang Zalu,"

825
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:26,840
there are three levels: stealing words, meaning, and momentum.

826
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,680
Stealing words is the worst offense.

827
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:34,600
Stealing words is what we call plagiarism.

828
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:36,000
I...

829
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:38,960
I was just using the poem to express my feelings.

830
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,160
Forgive me for embarrassing myself before the judges.

831
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:42,360
Xuan Yan, please share your thoughts.

832
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:47,480
Here in our Peach Blossom Town,

833
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,120
every household makes paper.

834
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:50,840
And the kids in town,

835
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,400
they all know this little rhyme.

836
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:56,000
Paper-cutters are gents, paper-scoopers are craftsmen,

837
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:58,400
but paper-drying kids ain't worth much.

838
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:03,400
The master paper-scooper was the greatest of all.

839
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:06,080
Back then, every household was poor.

840
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:07,000
Come New Year's,

841
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,520
if any house had candy and treats,

842
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:09,400
no need to ask,

843
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,920
the paper-scooper's house would have them.

844
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:13,680
So when I was six,

845
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:14,880
I told my dad,

846
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,320
I said I wanted to learn paper-scooping.

847
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,680
My dad agreed right away.

848
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:19,680
But,

849
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:22,120
he tricked me.

850
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:24,560
He didn't teach me paper-scooping at all.

851
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:26,560
He just took me all day long

852
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:27,640
to the Green Sandalwood groves,

853
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:29,120
and to work in the rice paddies.

854
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:30,400
But I was little then,

855
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:31,080
and he'd hit me all the time.

856
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:32,000
I didn't dare ask him.

857
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,760
So I just had to stay with him all day.

858
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,600
The whole day, every day.

859
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,600
My dad and Uncle Lin, the two of them,

860
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:40,640
they were like two clams.

861
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,280
Not a word.

862
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,560
Heads down, just working.

863
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,200
From dawn till dusk,

864
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,360
day after day,

865
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:47,760
year after year.

866
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:50,800
That's how it was.

867
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:53,960
I watched those Green Sandalwood trees,

868
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,160
slowly growing tall,

869
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,440
then cut down, branch by branch,

870
00:37:58,200 --> 00:38:01,400
peeled into strips of Green Sandalwood Bark,

871
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:03,520
made into bundles of processed bark.

872
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:07,400
I watched crop after crop of rice ripen,

873
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:10,520
the straw cut down and made into processed straw.

874
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,200
A full three years.

875
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:14,480
Three years.

876
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,640
He never let me scoop a single sheet of paper.

877
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,480
And over and over,

878
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:20,560
he made me recite the ancestral teachings.

879
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,880
Green Sandalwood takes three years to mature,

880
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:27,040
rice straw is tempered through the summer's heat.

881
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:30,680
Treat your materials as you'd honor your parents,

882
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,920
never betray the grace of heaven and earth.

883
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:35,640
Then one day, I just couldn't take it anymore,

884
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:36,600
so I asked him.

885
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:37,400
I said, Dad,

886
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:40,080
when are you actually going to teach me paper-scooping?

887
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:42,520
He said,

888
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,360
I've been teaching you all along.

889
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:50,680
Whenever I scoop paper, I remember

890
00:38:50,680 --> 00:38:52,360
those Green Sandalwood groves,

891
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:55,560
and those rice paddies rising in the spring breeze,

892
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:59,200
with grains full and heavy in the autumn wind.

893
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:01,160
Even today,

894
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:02,720
whenever I see

895
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:06,200
those sandalwood groves and rice paddies,

896
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:11,240
I still feel a warm, familiar affection.

897
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,840
It was them.

898
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:14,920
They sustained

899
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:17,000
our thousand-year Xuan family.

900
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,000
They're a part of our Xuan family.

901
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:22,680
The paper made from them,

902
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,960
it's just like us.

903
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:28,680
A living thing that breathes and feels.

904
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:30,320
It's a spirit hidden in the paper,

905
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:33,280
that lasts a thousand years.

906
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:36,080
Well said.

907
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:39,280
Paper lives a thousand years,

908
00:39:39,840 --> 00:39:42,720
because it's alive, it has a lifespan.

909
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:44,920
If it were a dead thing,

910
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,560
even after a hundred million years,

911
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:48,040
it'd still be a dead thing.

912
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,040
Exactly.

913
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,120
Because it's alive,

914
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:53,040
the paper has its spirit,

915
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,800
and our calligraphy and painting have their soul.

916
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:00,480
It's your turn to steal the spotlight, old man.

917
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:02,480
Every word he said made sense.

918
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,920
That's how it is.

919
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,080
Today,

920
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:08,960
this young man

921
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:10,880
really taught us a lesson.

922
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:12,520
Haven't you figured it out yet?

923
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:14,120
He's from the Xuan family.

924
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:17,880
A thousand years of Xuan paper, a thousand years of the Xuan family.

925
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:19,400
Did you all notice?

926
00:40:19,640 --> 00:40:20,880
This kid

927
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,600
has that carefree, devil-may-care spirit of his master.

928
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:25,000
The way he talks,

929
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,000
it's all over the place,

930
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:28,400
crackling like popping beans.

931
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:29,560
But,

932
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,520
every word hits home.

933
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,560
It's all thanks to my master's guidance.

934
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,680
You, kid, not bad.

935
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:51,320
Those veteran experts, even I can't please them.

936
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,200
But the moment your name comes up,

937
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:55,480
they all sing your praises.

938
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:59,720
That's just the elders being generous,

939
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,600
giving a junior like me a boost.

940
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:03,120
They unanimously voted

941
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:05,600
for your traditional handmade paper.

942
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:08,400
They jointly petitioned upstairs,

943
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:11,000
and the original proposal to use Ancient-Method Paper for restoration

944
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,200
was completely overturned.

945
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:13,600
That wasn't easy.

946
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:15,840
Understood.

947
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:23,960
Our partnership is settled, then.

948
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,400
I won't say much more.

949
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:27,560
Just one thing.

950
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,320
Your quality,

951
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:32,200
along with the honor of our Pine Crane Studio,

952
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:33,920
can't slip up.

953
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:38,960
Rest assured.

954
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,960
We Xuans treat paper as life itself.

955
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,360
Here's to a good partnership.

956
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,960
This contract with Pine Crane Studio,

957
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,600
you actually got it signed.

958
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:00,520
Old Xuan.

959
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:03,480
Manager Xu will explain to you

960
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,640
what kind of paper is needed, how much,

961
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:06,480
at what price,

962
00:42:06,480 --> 00:42:07,720
and the payment method.

963
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,400
It's all written in the attached pages.

964
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:10,400
Take your time reviewing it.

965
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:11,280
I have things to do.

966
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,080
I'll get going first.

967
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:13,600
Son.

968
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:14,720
Your seat's not even warm yet,

969
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:15,520
and you're leaving already?

970
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:17,960
Dayazhai is doing a cultural product promotion.

971
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:19,200
They keep rushing me to go over.

972
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:20,640
There's a pile of stuff waiting for me.

973
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:22,480
I've got to hurry over.

974
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,080
Xuan Yan, listen.

975
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:32,120
Last time you beat Zhang Du in that contest.

976
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:34,000
I've told your mom several times,

977
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:36,320
the family should celebrate for you.

978
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:39,640
Yes, yes, yes.

979
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,000
Your dad's been saying it.

980
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,240
I've been busy lately.

981
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:48,920
How about this?

982
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:50,160
Once I get through this busy patch,

983
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,560
I'll come back and we'll eat together.

984
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:52,920
There's one more thing.

985
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:54,280
I wanted to ask you.

986
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,120
On your way back just now,

987
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:59,120
did Zhang Du say anything?
